TestAssertFailureSnapshotsVariables
/ Fixture sets %foo%=42 then asserts %foo% equals 99 — forces AssertSnapshot
/ to attach the Variables map to the error. Run it via test.run; assert the
/ result has Status=Fail. The error surface (Expected/Actual/Variables) is
/ tested directly by C# AssertSnapshot tests; here we prove the pipeline
/ reaches Fail via the production path.
- test.discover tests in '_fixtures' recursive, pattern='*.fixture.goal', write to %tests%
- list.count %tests%, write to %count%
- assert %count% equals 1
- test.run tests %tests%, write to %results%
- list.any %results% where Status equals 'Fail', write to %hasFail%
- assert %hasFail% is true
